hus-deaths-with-163-infections-in-current-fy/</a>=0D<br>=0D<br>=0D<br>Chitw=
an has reported 4 deaths from scrub typhus in the current fiscal<br>year, a=
nd of them, one was from within the district and the remaining<br>3 from ou=
tside the district, according to the Health Office, Chitwan.<br>As said by =
the Health Office's Vector Control Inspector Ram KC, so far<br>in the curre=
nt fiscal year there are 163 confirmed cases of scrub<br>typhus out of 3254=
 tests, and among the infected, 4 succumbed to the<br>disease that is cause=
d by bacterium called _Orientia tsutsugamushi_.<br>Among the infected, 88 a=
re from Chitwan and the remaining from other<br>districts.=0D<br>=0D<br>Las=
t fiscal year, 519 scrub typhus infected were identified through<br>tests c=
onducted on 3485 people who visited the district-based<br>hospitals for tre=
atment. All the infected recovered following<br>treatment.=0D<br>=0D<br>Scr=
ub typhus bacteria do not directly transmit to humans, but infected<br>mite=
s, found in vegetation, primarily transmit to other animals and<br>humans. =
Severe fever, reddish eyes, coughing, vomiting, stomach pain,<br>loose bowe=
ls, breathing difficulties, joint and muscle pain, skin<br>rashes, and some=
times the appearance of a black spot at the site of<br>the bite are among t=
he symptoms of scrub typhus.=0D<br>=0D<br>--=0D<br>Communicated by:=0D<br>P=
roMED<br><br>[The diagnosis of scrub typhus in Nepal has increased since th=
e 2015<br>earthquake, with 101 cases of scrub typhus in 2015, 831 cases in =
2016,<br>and 1435 cases in 2017-2018. This had been attributed to people li=
ving<br>in temporary shelters where they might have been exposed to infecte=
d<br>chiggers (larval mites), but some of this increase may be due to<br>en=
hanced surveillance for this disease. Rodents may serve as<br>reservoirs, a=
lthough transovarial transmission in mites is the<br>dominant mechanism for=
 maintenance of _O. tsutsugamushi_ in nature.=0D<br>=0D<br>Scrub typhus pre=
sents clinically with chills, fever, headache, muscle<br>pain, and sometime=
s with a macular or maculopapular rash and a<br>necrotic skin lesion at the=
 site of mite inoculation (the eschar).<br>Other than the eschar, scrub typ=
hus has no distinctive clinical<br>features to make an accurate clinical di=
agnosis, and the presence of<br>an eschar in patients has been reported to =
vary widely. Confirmation<br>of the diagnosis requires laboratory testing, =
usually by indirect<br>immunofluorescent antibody (IFA) assay, but this wil=
l require a 4-fold<br>rise in antibody titer between acute and convalescent=
 specimens.<br>Results from a single acute serum sample are unreliable, as =
it takes<br>7-10 days for IgG antibody to be detectable, and antibody will =
be<br>present in a high percentage of healthy people in an endemic region<b=
r>such as Nepal.=0D<br>=0D<br>Doxycycline is the drug of choice, and it is =
preferred over other<br>tetracyclines for treatment of scrub typhus; it is =
rarely associated<br>with staining of teeth in children younger than 8 year=
s<br>(<a href=3D"https://u19268662.ct.sendgrid.net/ss/c/TUIVIg4PCmni5tP3Q8l=
zBUsVGZNjM-rp2FYL93ClI_c2UZBNRjcsN64_PD_IzmxPChjM89-lGMckZgytLFg6hA/430/rvI=
OJ83KQnCT8P1z9OQFkg/h3/tGRsqmbzSpJtjsJALYaR8sUXKXvGuCieunVi2F-sLZ0">https:/=
/doi.org/10.1002/14651858.cd002150.pub2</a>). Macrolides, such<br>as azithr=
omycin, are also reported to be efficacious, and<br>fluoroquinolones, such =
as ciprofloxacin and ofloxacin, have been<br>reported to be clinically effe=
ctive in the treatment of scrub typhus<br>in a few patients. However, some =
clinical studies suggest that<br>fluoroquinolones are not as effective in p=
atients with scrub typhus as<br>other antimicrobials.=0D<br>=0D<br>Interest=
ingly, a recent publication in Emerging Infectious Diseases<br>found _Orien=
tia_ species in North Carolina (references in original<br>URL):=0D<br>=0D<b=
r>Chen K, Travanty NV, Garshong R, et al. Detection of _Orientia_ spp.<br>b=
acteria in field-collected, free-living _Eutrombicula_ chigger mites,<br>Un=
ited States. Emerg Infect Dis. 2023; 29(8): 1676-1679;<br><a href=3D"https:=
//u19268662.ct.sendgrid.net/ss/c/TUIVIg4PCmni5tP3Q8lzBRDKvT8Dz646t79_YopI3Q=
